@GiudGiud I Change execute_on as default, some changes occurred, but Picard still didn't converge, and eventually main app didn't converge in a non-linear iteration step, and I break the running, as shown in the run log:
log_default_trans_post.txt
I tried adding more execute_on also, still not convergent.

@WayneX-Wong one thing to try is to run a relaxation transient, with 'fake' time steps where only 1 fixed point iteration is taken on every time step.
Another thing is underrelaxation.
I think you may need to specify which variables to relax (with relaxed_variables or transformed_variables parameters), it wont do all by default

